So since I use static site generator with full control over the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, even the content management service is handled by hugo with Makrdown language and a flexible shortcode by Blowfish Theme. I can use GitHub Actions to automate the build and deployment process.&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hanifnaoh.com/posts/blogportfolio-cloudflare-github-actions/featured.png"/></item><item><title>Lore's Quests</title><link>https://hanifnaoh.com/projects/lores-quests/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://hanifnaoh.com/projects/lores-quests/</guid><description>&lt;figure>
